          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to validate whether a given input string corresponds to a \"Yes\" or \"No\" value, typically used in scenarios where data needs to be standardized or validated against specific criteria."
        }
