    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead when used in large queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a result set. However, given the simplicity of this function, the performance impact is minimal. It is important to ensure that the function is not used excessively in large datasets or within complex queries to avoid potential performance degradation."
